Enumeration Type Documentation

enum boolT

Boolean enumeration data type.

This enumeration data type is an implementation of a boolean data type. The program can use it, in order to declare variables with `true' or `false' values.

Enumerator:
false  It means that something is false.
true  It means that something is true.
